parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially during rain or snow, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wiper motor fails to operate intermittently
the windshield wipers perform erratically
the windshield wipers quit without warning
the windshield wipers come on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Defect (Separation of Glass from Laminate)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the glass from the laminate can cause the windshield to bubble, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield is separating from the laminate
causing the windshield to bubble.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.

the brake pedal feels soft or spongy

the brakes are not responding as expected.

the brake lights are intermittent or faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Seat Track and Locking Mechanism Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat track and locking mechanism can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, potentially leading to loss of control while driving, or injury in the event of sudden stops or accidents.
symptoms: The seat moves back and forth on the track
the seat is hard to lock in place
the seat wiggles or has excessive movement even when locked
the seat collapses or falls backward without warning.
